# Do not reuse desktop layout patterns on mobile

## Intent

On **small viewports** (especially **base** / **`max-lg`**, and the **player portal** phone shell), **do not** clone desktop UX in a shrunken form: cramped multi-column grids, sidebar + detail side-by-side, wide tables scaled down, hover-menus turned into tiny lists, dense “dashboard tiles” in one view.

Mobile should get **purpose-built**, **thumb-friendly** structure—not the same DOM/layout compressed.

## Prefer (mobile-native)

| Desktop-style pattern | Prefer on phone / small screens |
|------------------------|----------------------------------|
| Sidebar + main | Bottom or top tabs, stacked sections, sheet/drawer for secondary |
| Wide data table | Card list, one row per entity, essential fields only |
| Multi-column form | Single column, full width, stepped flow if needed |
| Hover dropdown / mega menu | Full-width list, modal, or bottom sheet |
| 3-column dashboard | One primary scroll; drill-in for more |

## How to implement

- **Mobile-first CSS:** Default (or **`max-lg`**) defines the **simple** layout; **`lg:`** / **`xl:`** **add** columns, sidebars, density—do not rely on squishing the desktop layout below **`lg`**.
- **Separate structure** is OK when the product requires it (e.g. totally different nav on `lg`); **shrinking** the desktop tree is not.

## Player portal

For **`components/portal/player-portal/**`** and **`app/(free-portal)/player/**`**: keep **bottom navigation + single main column**. Do not introduce desktop-style dual-pane or sticky side rails on **`max-lg`** unless explicitly desktop-only behind **`lg:`** with a **different** mobile structure at base.

